;################################################### DESCRIPTION
@Node "1_Description" "Well, spank my arse!"

                         @{b}╗ÀDÀEÀSÀCÀRÀIÀPÀTÀIÀOÀNÀ>@{ub}

  Y'know, how come programs with loads of features look crap?

  A  program  will  either  look  good and be crap, or be look crap and be
  good.   On  my  ever  eternal  quest,  I'm going to try and rectify this
  situation.

  @{i}Trinity  Player@{ui}  is  a  program  that (hopefully) looks great, and works
  great  too!   Obviously  everyones'  tastes  differ,  so that's why I've
  included  the  GUI  graphics  for you, so you can design your own if you
  want to.

  Oh sorry, I went off track there.

  @{i}Trinity  Player@{ui}  is  a  CD  player  that works with all SCSI/ATAPI CDROM
  drives and has quite a few features to mess about with.

  @{b}PLEASE   NOTE:@{ub}    @{i}Trinity  Player@{ui}  and  this  AmigaGuide  doc  file  are
  un-finished,  which  means  there's  sections  missing  and  things  not
  currently implemented.  Please watch out for updates (see @{"Author" link "5_Author"}) !
@EndNode

;################################################### REQUIREMENTS
@Node "1_Requirements" "Aha!  I'M Alan Partridge! .... er, no I'm not. Sorry."

                 @{b}<ÀSÀYÀSÀTÀEÀMÀ ÀRÀEÀQÀUÀIÀRÀEÀMÀEÀNÀTÀSÀ½@{ub}

  @{u}@{b}Hardware@{uu}@{ub}:
    Amiga with OS v2.04+
    SCSI/ATAPI CDROM drive
    Er... at least 1 audio CD!

  @{u}@{b}Software@{uu}@{ub}:
    Diskfont.library            - goes in LIBS:
    Mathtrans.library           - goes in LIBS:  (maybe required)

  @{u}@{b}Other@{uu}@{ub}:
    You will need an Interlaced screenmode (e.g..  640x512) with the
    MagicWB (8 colours minimum) palette.

  You  @{u}CAN@{uu}  use @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} on a non-interlaced screen (with or
  without the MagicWB palette), but it'll look shite!
@EndNode

;################################################### FEATURES
@Node "1_Features" "I'm a Creature Feature! (TM)"

                            @{b}½ÀFÀEÀAÀTÀUÀRÀEÀSÀ╗@{ub}

  ° @{fg shine}Looks great!@{fg text}
  °áHas standard CD player controls
    (Stop/Pause/Skip Back/Rewind/Play/Fast Forward/Skip Forward).
  °á@{fg shine}CDs can be ejected via the GUI.@{fg text}
  °áExtensive keyboard support (use the Function keys to play the
    corresponding tracks, use the Numeric Keypad, etc.).
  °á@{fg shine}Each CD can have it's own ID file (compatible with MCDPlayer,
    Skandalfo Player, MegaCD Player, etc.)  which is loaded when a
    valid Compact Disc is inserted. User specified path.@{fg text}
  °áA nice Song Editor which lets you edit the  current  CD's  ID
    file.  Tracks can also be played if the right mouse button is
    pressed while in the Song Editor.
  °á@{fg shine}CDs can be played/stopped/ejected on program start-up/exit.@{fg text}
  °áA Program Mode editor which lets  you  specify  which  tracks
    to play and in which order.
  °á@{fg shine}Preview Mode lets you play a user specified number of seconds
    of each track (sometimes called "Intro" in other CD players).@{fg text}
  °áShuffle Mode which plays tracks in a random order.
  °á@{fg shine}Repeat Mode to repeat the current, er... mode.@{fg text}
  °áIf you don't like the GUI graphics,  you can draw your own or
    use someone else's instead !!
  °á@{fg shine}Two GUI sizes.  The  big  one (ooer!)  for  people  with  big
    screens  and  the  minimised  version  for  people with small
    screens (for people that need every inch of available space).@{fg text}
  °á@{i}Trinity Player@{ui} can be opened on any (public) screen,  or  can
    be told to open it's own 8-colour Interlaced MagicWB screen.
  °á@{fg shine}The main window can be moved around via the cursor  keys  and
    can be moved in 5 preset locations by using the keys 1-5.@{fg text}
  °á@{i}Trinity Player@{ui} checks for changes in the System Preferences.
    If there's been a change,  you'll  be  asked  if  you want to
    close-down the main window and then re-appear to reflect  the
    changes (if any).
  °á@{fg shine}Extensive ARexx port. There's so many commands, you can write
    your own interface for @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} via ARexx !!@{fg text}
  °áOn-line AmigaGuide documentation (not context sensitive - yet).
  °á@{fg shine}Partly font-sensitive.@{fg text}
  °áCommodity.
  °á@{fg shine}Only ú5 !@{fg text}

                         @{b}@{u}OTHER NON-PROGRAM FEATURES@{uu}@{ub}

  @{b}*@{ub}á@{i}Trinity Player@{ui} will be supported for a long time to come.
    So you can expect lots of regular updates!
  @{b}*@{ub}áBlitz Basic 2 source code @{u}may@{uu} soon be available for ú10.
  @{b}*@{ub} There will be a (small) @{i}Trinity Player@{ui} mailing list very soon.
@EndNode

